title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Make a Wayang Plan that take the cities in interesting_municipalities_cities textfile and returns all organisations which have a matching municipality in the textfile. The textfile only have cities, but a municipality is usually called something like the city. Output the result in a textfile.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; val mun = r.getField(2).toString; val base = mun.toLowerCase.replaceAll("\\bkommune\\b", "").trim; val tokens = base.split("[^a-zæøå]+").filter(_.nonEmpty).distinct; tokens.map(t => (t, (orgId, name, mun))) }
(a: (Int, String, String), b: (Int, String, String)) => a

log.thoughts: Read city names from the text file, tokenize them, tokenize municipalities (stripping the word “kommune”), join on shared tokens, deduplicate organisations, and output results to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, name, municipality FROM organisation) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; val mun = r.getField(2).toString; val base = mun.toLowerCase.replaceAll("\\bkommune\\b", "").trim; val tokens = base.split("[^a-zæøå]+").filter(_.nonEmpty).distinct; tokens.map(t => (t, (orgId, name, mun))) }
(a: (Int, String, String), b: (Int, String, String)) => a

title: Wayang: Wayang plan sent to Wayang
Err: Wayang error. Plan executed unsucessful
